The Vice President of the United States met with law enforcement leaders from across the country to discuss ways to improve trust between law enforcement and the communities they serve. The Vice President expressed gratitude for their service and acknowledged the burden they often bear in dealing with societal challenges. He discussed the importance of officer training and ensuring that police have the necessary resources for community policing. The Vice President reaffirmed his commitment to finding solutions to reduce anxiety for both law enforcement and the communities they protect, and plans to continue convening discussions with law enforcement and community leaders. The meeting was attended by various law enforcement leaders and administration participants, including the Vice President, White House Counsel, and representatives from the Department of Justice.